The Vocalm virtual audio drivers (VocalmMic.driver, VocalmSpeaker.driver) are
rebranded builds of BlackHole by Existential Audio Inc.
    https://github.com/ExistentialAudio/BlackHole
BlackHole is licensed under GPL-3.0. The driver components therefore remain
GPL-3.0; their complete corresponding source is the BlackHole source plus the
rename patches applied in build_drivers.sh (this repository).

The Vocalm application itself is a separate program that communicates with the
drivers only through the standard CoreAudio APIs.

Note for future commercial distribution: either keep publishing the driver
patches under GPL-3.0 (as here), license BlackHole commercially from
Existential Audio, or replace with a clean-room driver derived from Apple's
BSD-licensed AudioServerPlugIn sample code.
